title: For Sale:  AR15 Adams Arms Rifle
postcontent: This is a brand new unfired 16” 1/7 5.56 Adams Arms Complete Carbine Piston Upper with a Spikes Tactical complete lower. The piston system is self-cleaning, and has three settings: one for semi-auto Fire, one for suppressed fire, and one for single shot action. The hand guard is a Samson Star C-EX-P Free Float Carbine Length Rail that wraps around the gas block.The BCG is full auto design, no cut backs in that aspect, the back end of the BCG is wider, with the corners rounded so as to reduce carrier tilt and wear on the buffer tube when it passes the receiver in the tube. The Bolt is marked “M” for magnetic particle inspection.On the inside of the receiver, were the cam pin rotates into the little pocket on the side, Adams Arms rounded off that corner to assist with wear mitigation so the cam pin slides into place instead of wearing that corner down on the receiver wall making for a smother transition when locking and unlocking the bolt into position.The gas block is railed at receiver height, providing for continuous rail down the length of the rifle, with the adjustment knob at the end for quick and easy access. This is a very nice quality rifle. $1,000 for the whole package, or $800 for just the complete upper

title: For Sale:  Bond Arms Snake Slayer IV .45 Colt ONLY 4.25" Barrel +160 rounds of .45 colt
postcontent: I have a lightly used Bond Arms Snake Slayer IV for sale. This model has a 4.25" barrel and is 45 colt only, not the 45/410 model you usually see. The 45 colt only model is fully rifled which will deliver better bullet performance and prevent the tumbling often seen on the 45/410 models which only feature 1/2 inch of rifling. The great thing about the Bond derringer however is how easy it is to change the barrel, it takes all of 30 seconds to switch out barrels which are available in a wide variety of lengths and calibers, with enough barrels this derringer can potentially shoot 22, 32, 357,380, 9mm, 40mm, 10mm, 45 colt, 410 shot, and 45 acp in barrels between 2" to 6" with less than a minute to switch out.Included with the sale is a carrying case, 140 rounds of Hornady critical defense, 20 rounds of Hornady leverevolution, and 40 rounds of spent .45 colt brass. The derringer has had roughly 100 rounds fired through it.I really like this gun, and I plan on getting another soon, but for the time being Ruger recently starting making 3" .327 federal magnum SP101s again after a few years hiatus and I need some extra cash to get one.
